[Bill Mair&#39;s answer](https://stackoverflow.com/a/75836238/2422776) has the right idea - you need to return a smaller array without &quot;dangling&quot; elements. However, it may be easier to achieve this by streaming and filtering the array and then collecting it to an array than by creating a new array and then returning a partial copy of it:

    public static int[] overGivenMinutes(int minThres, int[] arrayValues){
        return Arrays.stream(arrayValues).filter(i -&gt; i / 60 &gt; minThres).toArray();
